## Instructions

### 1. Material Identification
Scan the entire image and catalog every distinct material type:
- **Wood**: hardwood floor, veneer, solid timber, plywood — note species if identifiable.
- **Stone**: marble, granite, travertine, slate, quartz composite.
- **Metal**: brushed steel, chrome, brass, copper, black iron.
- **Fabric**: upholstery, curtains, rugs, cushions — note weave type.
- **Glass**: clear, frosted, tinted, mirror.
- **Paint/Plaster**: wall paint, textured plaster, wallpaper.
- **Ceramic/Tile**: floor tile, wall tile, mosaic.
- **Leather**: natural, synthetic.
- **Plant/Organic**: live plants, dried elements.
- **Plastic/Composite**: acrylic, laminate, PVC.

### 2. Color Assignment
Assign each material category a distinct, saturated flat color:
- Wood → warm brown (#8B4513)
- Stone/Marble → cool gray (#A0A0C0)
- Metal → silver/blue (#708090)
- Fabric/Textile → soft pink (#DDA0DD)
- Glass → light cyan (#00CED1)
- Painted wall → light yellow (#FFFACD)
- Ceramic/Tile → orange (#FFA500)
- Leather → dark red (#8B0000)
- Plant/Organic → green (#228B22)
- Plastic/Composite → purple (#9370DB)
- Ceiling → white (#F5F5F5)
- Floor (generic) → tan (#D2B48C)

Adjust colors as needed to ensure all categories in this specific image are clearly distinguishable.

### 3. Generate Channel Map
- Fill each region of the image with its assigned flat color — no gradients, no shading, no texture.
- Maintain crisp boundaries between different materials.
- Preserve the exact geometry and perspective of the original image.
- Every pixel must be assigned to exactly one material category.

### 4. Add Color Legend
- Include a clear legend within the image (bottom or side panel).
- Each entry: color swatch + material name (in English).
- Sort legend entries by area covered (largest first).

## Quality Requirements
- Clean, artifact-free boundaries between material regions.
- 100% coverage — no unclassified pixels.
- Accurate material classification — surfaces correctly identified.
- Legend must be legible and complete.

## Constraints
- Output FLAT colors only — no lighting, shadows, gradients, or texture in the channel map.
- Maintain the same perspective and proportions as the input image.
- Every distinct material must have its own unique color.
- Output exactly one channel map image including the legend.
